A Durban hospital is being investigated after a video – showing a nurse allegedly abusing a patient – was widely shared on social media.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
The KwaZulu-Natal Department of Health said in statement on Wednesday that they “strongly condemned” the alleged conduct of a staff nurse from St Mary’s Hospital, which if true, would be in violation of the code of conduct of health care professionals. 
“The alleged incident, which took place on November 6, 2017, was captured on video and widely distributed on social media.”












